1
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:34,979
[How dare you!?]

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:39,940
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:40,780
Let go of me!

4
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,280
Dan!

5
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:42,479
-Your Majesty!
-Dan!

6
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:48,400
Mr. Bei,

7
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:50,520
you go.

8
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:53,720
Only you can save her.

9
00:01:54,479 --> 00:01:55,150
Please go, okay?

10
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:55,850
If I go,

11
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:57,220
who will protect you?

12
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,000
But Mr. Bei...

13
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:58,660
I cannot go!

14
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:06,970
Your Majesty...

15
00:02:09,009 --> 00:02:09,940
I'm begging you.

16
00:02:13,670 --> 00:02:15,600
I can't let anything happen to her.

17
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:21,000
Serving an emperor
is like walking with a tiger.

18
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,240
Does he like me,

19
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:26,280
or my foresight
that works only half the time?

20
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,430
I think you know the answer.

21
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:32,310
When the powerful clash,

22
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,780
people like us suffer.

23
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:34,840
At this point,

24
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:37,270
I no longer dream of a good match.

25
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:40,850
I just want to leave this dangerous place

26
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:43,670
and live out the rest of my life in peace.

27
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:47,960
Wanyin.

28
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:51,540
If you were so afraid,

29
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,480
why didn't you come to me?

30
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,000
Don't you have Consort Xie now?

31
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,460
She is just my strategist.

32
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,000
How shameless.

33
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:06,870
You look like

34
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:11,710
you're thinking of
how to continue deceiving me.

35
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:16,360
Fine.

36
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,360
Since you want to hear the truth,

37
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:21,829
I'll tell you.

38
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:29,310
I once, like Consort Xie,

39
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:32,520
foresaw your future—

40
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:36,140
turning the tide when all seemed lost

41
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:38,150
and receiving the people's homage.

42
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,710
It's just that...

43
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,310
What?

44
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,710
It's just that

45
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,800
the one standing beside you
to receive that homage

46
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,280
was not me.

47
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:00,510
Great answer.

48
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,220
It's the truth.

49
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:03,840
In this life,

50
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,560
I will stand beside no woman.

51
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,520
If there must be one,

52
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,250
it could only be you.

53
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:14,770
Why do you say that?

54
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:20,600
Because I've been waiting for you
for a long time.

55
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:25,480
More precisely,

56
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,520
it started 10 years ago, at 2 a.m.

57
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:32,360
on that night.

58
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,610
You both claimed you had foresight

59
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:43,430
and knew I was the chosen one.

60
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,510
Were those merely pleasing lies?

61
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,570
Then why did I believe them?

62
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:55,560
Why?

63
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,450
Because that was what I thought!

64
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:03,710
You only spoke
what was already in my heart.

65
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,640
Being the chosen one

66
00:05:06,350 --> 00:05:08,310
is simply where the people's support
comes together.

67
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,630
Whoever they want to be emperor

68
00:05:09,630 --> 00:05:10,750
becomes emperor.

69
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,190
So it's not that something happens

70
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:13,970
and then they believe.

71
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,410
Rather, because you believe,

72
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:19,870
it happens.

73
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Seven.

74
00:05:26,390 --> 00:05:28,800
When I was 7,
that lowly slave could pull my ear

75
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,130
and say I was born lowly.

76
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:33,680
Was I born lowly?

77
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:34,870
No.

78
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:37,830
It was the Empress Dowager and that tyrant

79
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,960
who made them believe I was born lowly.

80
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,270
So when I grew up,

81
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,360
I learned how to change my fate.

82
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:48,800
That means

83
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:55,159
having the very best of everything:

84
00:05:58,830 --> 00:05:59,600
fame,

85
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,720
achievements,

86
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,190
and women.

87
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,870
Only then

88
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,360
would the whole world

89
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,470
direct their will toward me.

90
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:18,160
Speaking of Xiahou Bo,

91
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,880
people naturally say

92
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,440
that Prince Duan
is not only far from lowly,

93
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:24,920
but extremely noble—

94
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,070
so noble that none can reach him,

95
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:36,490
so noble that he is the chosen one,

96
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:40,820
the one the people believe
will become emperor.

97
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,120
Wanyin,

98
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:48,290
do you want to be the most honored woman
in the world,

99
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,460
or just a footnote in history,

100
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,280
a little-known demonic consort

101
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,430
who dies young?

102
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:04,920
Your Highness Prince Duan!

103
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,480
Your Highness Prince Duan!

104
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:14,310
I am here to pick up the Noble Consort!

105
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:26,430
Thank you, Your Highness Prince Duan,

106
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,220
for saving Her Highness.

107
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,240
I have been sent by His Majesty's decree

108
00:07:32,159 --> 00:07:34,180
to take Her Highness

109
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,560
back to the palace!

110
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,620
The Emperor sent people to claim you.

111
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,810
Tell me, should I hand you over or not?

112
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,640
I was suddenly attacked.

113
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,120
It's understandable

114
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,720
that he sent people.

115
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:53,430
Rest assured, Your Highness.

116
00:07:53,430 --> 00:07:54,790
I won't tell anyone

117
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:58,130
what we said today
after I leave the carriage.

118
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,780
Then does that mean

119
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,720
you are not going to consider me?

120
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,610
Since you call it "considering,"

121
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:08,680
why not give me more time?

122
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,240
With the Imperial Guards outside,

123
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,970
now is truly not the right moment
to discuss this.

124
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,040
If you don't mind,

125
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,560
we can continue communicating

126
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,310
by secret letters
after I return to the palace.

127
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,310
What do you think?

128
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:25,120
Of course I don't mind.

129
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,480
Well then...

130
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:36,200
take care.

131
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,480
10 years ago,

132
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,240
[In Memory of Li, Mother of Prince]

133
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:51,890
[Ten years ago]

134
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:49,480
at 2 a.m.

135
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,390
So this is the Second Prince?

136
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,930
Why isn't there a nanny looking after him?

137
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:02,440
His birth mother was a palace maid.

138
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:04,870
She thought giving birth to a prince
would make her noble,

139
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:07,070
but the Empress had her beaten to death.

140
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,870
Everyone in the palace tries to avoid him.

141
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:11,670
Who would want to be associated
with such bad luck?

142
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,760
He really was born lowly.

143
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:15,400
Let's go.

144
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:21,610
Master,

145
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:23,080
I was the one dozing off.

146
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,200
You punished the wrong person.

147
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,200
The Crown Prince has a noble status.

148
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,840
Even if he makes mistakes,

149
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,900
the punishment should be taken by
his study companion.

150
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:51,840
I...

151
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:52,940
I...

152
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,850
work—serve...

153
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
in a nearby side hall.

154
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:59,590
You can't even learn these few lines?

155
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,290
I can learn them.

156
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,320
Remember,

157
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,300
you're very scared.

158
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,770
Speak haltingly.

159
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:10,150
I work in a nearby side hall.

160
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:12,170
I often saw

161
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,760
a wandering figure there

162
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,040
and grew curious.

163
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,450
So I dug a little when no one was around.

164
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,550
We're the same kind.

165
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:19,210
How are you?

166
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:21,910
What's the second half of "study hard"?

167
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:22,670
I don't understand.

168
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:23,840
What holiday is June 1st?

169
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,770
Your Highness, you're hurting me.

170
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,050
You're all I have in this world.

171
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,310
I'll go get someone!

172
00:10:30,550 --> 00:10:31,000
Stop!

173
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:31,870
No.

174
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:33,670
No, no one can know.

175
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:34,840
No one can know.

176
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,600
I killed someone?

177
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:41,170
I didn't mean to.

178
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,850
I didn't mean to!

179
00:10:57,790 --> 00:10:58,790
Your Highness...

180
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,770
I've done as you said.

181
00:11:12,870 --> 00:11:13,960
The same kind?

182
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,170
Xiahou Dan.

183
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,660
What kind of
"same kind" are you looking for?

184
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:26,890
Your Highness.

185
00:11:27,550 --> 00:11:29,750
The person you just shot has been saved.

186
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:31,720
What did he find?

187
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,960
Consort Yu had a mechanism
hidden in her sleeve,

188
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,360
which we've seen before.

189
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:37,930
Judging by its design,

190
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:40,490
it seems capable
of shooting hidden arrows.

191
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,940
Your Highness.

192
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,680
Go deliver the message to the generals.

193
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:48,150
Yes.

194
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,910
Since this is your choice,

195
00:11:53,790 --> 00:11:55,390
I shall grant it.

196
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:19,680
[Wucheng Gate]

197
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,480
I was wrong.

198
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:52,870
I shouldn't have left the palace
without permission.

199
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,450
You deserve to die.

200
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:07,600
I failed to take proper care
of Her Highness.

201
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,530
I deserve to die!

202
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:09,440
No.

203
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,930
It was my own decision to go out.

204
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,720
They didn't know about your order.

205
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,850
I'm the one at fault.

206
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,440
Bury them all.

207
00:13:21,230 --> 00:13:22,510
[Wucheng Gate]

208
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,080
Wait! Wait!

209
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:27,670
I said it has nothing to do with them.

210
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:31,520
Your Majesty.

211
00:13:31,670 --> 00:13:32,470
Your Majesty!

212
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,320
We only have this many secret guards,

213
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,670
and we've already lost most of them.

214
00:13:35,670 --> 00:13:36,720
These are the people who

215
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,670
died for you in the original story.

216
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:39,530
But they let Prince Duan find you.

217
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:40,550
Prince Duan found me because

218
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,240
his spies were searching the entire city.

219
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,480
It has nothing to do
with these secret guards.

220
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,870
Letting you leave the palace
in this situation

221
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:48,440
is no different from treason.

222
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:50,120
I said it was my own idea.

223
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,240
One takes responsibility
for one's own actions.

224
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,440
Just punish me alone.

225
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,920
What's the use of punishing you?

226
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,920
You're so shameless.

227
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,770
Will you learn your lesson?

228
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:19,320
[Taiji Hall]

229
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:18,240
I want you to remember

230
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,700
that when you do something wrong,

231
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,050
I will punish the people

232
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,030
you care about.

233
00:14:50,550 --> 00:14:52,080
What are you talking about?

234
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:57,470
Do you really think you are that tyrant?

235
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:03,870
I am a tyrant.

236
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:10,240
I always have been.

237
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:17,500
♪ Tell me ♪

238
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:21,660
♪ Why so many laments echo in the wind ♪

239
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:22,950
What are you waiting for?

240
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:24,420
♪ Walk past me ♪

241
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:28,450
♪ Like an aloof passerby ♪

242
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,700
Take them away!

243
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:31,330
[Wucheng Gate]

244
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:32,270
♪ Don't watch me as the rain falls ♪

245
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,800
♪ Love burns too hot as it passes ♪

246
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:42,340
♪ Even a lifetime of war
cannot be extinguished ♪

247
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,610
♪ Blame me ♪

248
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:48,770
♪ For the frailty of fate ♪

249
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:51,410
♪ Hide me ♪

250
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:55,870
♪ With light snow or thick ink ♪

251
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:56,860
I acted

252
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:59,670
♪ We met in the crowd ♪

253
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:00,410
ignorant and reckless

254
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:03,170
♪ There's no mistake in this life ♪

255
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,390
and disobeyed Your Majesty.

256
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:07,050
♪ I only regret being clumsy in words ♪

257
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:06,270
Please punish me, Your Majesty.

258
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:09,190
♪ And shrinking from speaking it out ♪

259
00:16:09,610 --> 00:16:11,990
♪ Even when destiny mocked me, hurt me ♪

260
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:13,920
♪ Destroyed me, or trapped me ♪

261
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:16,420
♪ I never yielded ♪

262
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,200
♪ But why ♪

263
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:22,900
♪ Can't I bear to see
even a single tear in your eyes? ♪

264
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:22,580
[Wucheng Gate]

265
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:25,750
♪ But we once fell in love, went wild ♪

266
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,270
Alright.

267
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,600
♪ Split up, and lost each other ♪

268
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:29,980
♪ They are
all unforgettable memories to me ♪

269
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:32,130
♪ The first time I met you ♪

270
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:42,050
♪ It felt like something suddenly
lit up my soul ♪

271
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,000
Eunuch An.

272
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:39,250
[Taiji Hall]

273
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:39,890
Confine Noble Consort Yu to her chamber.

274
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:41,550
Lock it.

275
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:43,980
From this day forward,

276
00:16:44,830 --> 00:16:46,530
until the moment I die,

277
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,770
she is not allowed to step outside.

278
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,320
Thank you,

279
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,790
Your Majesty, for your grace.

280
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:56,510
♪ Blame me ♪

281
00:16:57,180 --> 00:17:00,680
♪ For the frailty of fate ♪

282
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:03,360
♪ Hide me ♪

283
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:07,880
♪ With light snow or thick ink ♪

284
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,040
Your Majesty!

285
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,560
♪ We met in the crowd ♪

286
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:10,760
I'm begging you.

287
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:15,099
♪ There's no mistake in this life ♪

288
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,930
I can't let anything happen to her.

289
00:17:16,010 --> 00:17:18,990
♪ I only regret being clumsy in words ♪

290
00:17:19,010 --> 00:17:21,130
♪ And shrinking from speaking it out ♪

291
00:17:21,579 --> 00:17:24,000
♪ Even when destiny mocked me, hurt me ♪

292
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:27,560
[Taiji Hall]

293
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:25,810
♪ Destroyed me, or trapped me ♪

294
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:28,359
♪ I never yielded ♪

295
00:17:28,670 --> 00:17:30,190
♪ But why ♪

296
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:34,940
♪ Can't I bear to see
even a single tear in your eyes? ♪

297
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:37,660
♪ But we once fell in love, went wild ♪

298
00:17:37,710 --> 00:17:39,560
♪ Split up, and lost each other ♪

299
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:41,920
♪ They are
all unforgettable memories to me ♪

300
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:44,090
♪ The first time I met you ♪

301
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:52,890
♪ It felt like something suddenly
lit up my soul ♪

302
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,510
I want you to remember

303
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,670
[Taiji Hall]

304
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:28,970
that when you do something wrong,

305
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:29,940
I will punish

306
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:33,570
the people you care about.

307
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:38,110
If she doesn't stay for the night...

308
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:39,550
must she be executed?

309
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,590
We're together now?

310
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:45,510
Oh my.

311
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,160
I've become love-obsessed after all.

312
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:48,690
No matter

313
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,680
who sits on that throne,

314
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:51,960
you

315
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,140
will still be yourselves—

316
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,030
honest and capable talents.

317
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:59,440
Even knowing my fate ends in death,

318
00:20:00,590 --> 00:20:02,900
I want to do more before I die.

319
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:05,410
I'll risk my life to accompany you.

320
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:08,280
I've just returned to the palace

321
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:10,650
and heard about what happened to Mei.

322
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,740
Mei can't stay in the palace anymore.

323
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,310
I'll find a chance to send her away.

324
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:16,710
What are you waiting for?

325
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:17,580
Take them away!

326
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:19,520
[Wucheng Gate]

327
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,730
You only see her as a little bird

328
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:23,510
that needs to be set free,

329
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:24,790
but you fail to see

330
00:20:25,590 --> 00:20:27,190
how upright and noble she is—

331
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,460
radiant as the sun,

332
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:31,650
able to light up the vast blue sky.

333
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:33,400
No.

334
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,980
This isn't Xiahou Dan.

335
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,240
I don't believe it.

336
00:20:40,450 --> 00:20:42,130
Your Highness, where are you going?

337
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:43,330
I'm going to find him!

338
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,400
I don't believe
he can't tell right from wrong.

339
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,830
He is absolutely not a tyrant.

340
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:47,760
Absolutely not!

341
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,840
I don't care what others say,

342
00:20:55,070 --> 00:20:56,670
and I don't care what you say.

343
00:20:57,030 --> 00:20:59,550
I only believe
what I've seen with my own eyes.

344
00:20:59,550 --> 00:20:59,930
You,

345
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,110
Xiahou Dan,

346
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,130
is definitely not that kind of person!

347
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:07,420
[Yongyan Hall]

348
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,160
Mr. Bei,

349
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:19,310
I need to see him.

350
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:20,030
Wanyin,

351
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:21,680
Dan said

352
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:24,690
he doesn't want anyone to go in.

353
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:25,750
Am I just anyone?

354
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,700
Don't come closer.

355
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:09,810
You always drive me away
when something happens.

356
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,070
Don't you know any other tricks?

357
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:13,420
I don't want you to see.

358
00:22:40,410 --> 00:22:41,870
Does your head still hurt?

359
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:43,640
Yes.

360
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,410
How long has this been going on?

361
00:23:11,030 --> 00:23:12,290
It has been for a while.

362
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:15,880
Every time it acts up,

363
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,200
I lose control.

364
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,720
You should have told me earlier.

365
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,640
I'm not that fragile.

366
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:38,550
Don't cry.

367
00:23:40,340 --> 00:23:42,350
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

368
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,250
I'm sorry.

369
00:23:42,710 --> 00:23:43,960
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

370
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:46,430
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

371
00:23:44,310 --> 00:23:45,170
It was my fault.

372
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:46,960
I said those terrible things.

373
00:23:46,810 --> 00:23:48,130
♪ Drinking alone, hard to get drunk ♪

374
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:50,710
♪ Words unspoken ♪

375
00:23:48,970 --> 00:23:51,170
I regretted it the moment I turned away.

376
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,160
I was wrong too.

377
00:23:52,150 --> 00:23:54,630
♪ Shyness unhidden ♪

378
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:55,920
I shouldn't have left the palace.

379
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,460
♪ Walking down a street together ♪

380
00:23:57,550 --> 00:23:58,740
I misjudged the situation

381
00:23:58,740 --> 00:23:59,880
♪ Shoulder to shoulder ♪

382
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:00,670
and nearly caused a disaster.

383
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:02,240
♪ Raising my head, lowering my eyes ♪

384
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,880
I pushed you closer

385
00:24:02,740 --> 00:24:04,120
♪ Blushing slightly ♪

386
00:24:04,330 --> 00:24:06,660
♪ A face flushed red at first sight ♪

387
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:05,770
to becoming a tyrant.

388
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:06,830
No, Wanyin.

389
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:11,520
♪ A smile like a flower in my heart ♪

390
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,680
I was already a drowning man.

391
00:24:12,140 --> 00:24:15,510
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

392
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,750
You were the one pulling me ashore.

393
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:19,240
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

394
00:24:19,770 --> 00:24:21,560
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

395
00:24:21,810 --> 00:24:23,450
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

396
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:24,260
Then never become that tyrant.

397
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:25,490
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

398
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:25,960
I'm not afraid of failure,

399
00:24:25,660 --> 00:24:27,900
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

400
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,290
nor am I afraid of death.

401
00:24:28,290 --> 00:24:31,410
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

402
00:24:29,030 --> 00:24:31,290
But I'm afraid of losing you before that.

403
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:34,590
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

404
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:35,680
If you disappear,

405
00:24:34,710 --> 00:24:35,880
♪ Still unchanged ♪

406
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:39,150
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

407
00:24:37,550 --> 00:24:39,150
it means I'll disappear too,

408
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:41,190
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

409
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:42,070
fading away inside this shell.

410
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:45,510
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

411
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:45,550
Okay.

412
00:24:48,510 --> 00:24:50,120
We mustn't become others.

413
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:56,830
I'm CEO Dan,

414
00:24:59,270 --> 00:25:00,330
and you're Wanyin.

415
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,550
Even if

416
00:25:02,330 --> 00:25:04,420
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

417
00:25:04,270 --> 00:25:05,200
one day I die,

418
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:05,930
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

419
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:06,510
I...

420
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:08,430
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

421
00:25:08,790 --> 00:25:10,180
♪ Drinking alone, hard to get drunk ♪

422
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:12,660
♪ Words unspoken ♪

423
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:16,590
♪ Shyness unhidden ♪

424
00:25:18,290 --> 00:25:20,420
♪ Walking down a street together ♪

425
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:21,270
Without my permission,

426
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:21,870
♪ Shoulder to shoulder ♪

427
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:24,250
♪ Raising my head, lowering my eyes ♪

428
00:25:22,510 --> 00:25:23,970
you're not allowed to die.

429
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,130
♪ Blushing slightly ♪

430
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:28,670
♪ A face flushed red at first sight ♪

431
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:33,710
♪ A smile like a flower in my heart ♪

432
00:25:34,150 --> 00:25:37,650
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

433
00:25:38,230 --> 00:25:41,230
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

434
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,610
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

435
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,400
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

436
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:47,410
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

437
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,860
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

438
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:53,440
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

439
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,650
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

440
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,840
♪ Still unchanged ♪

441
00:25:58,320 --> 00:26:01,210
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

442
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:03,230
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

443
00:26:03,340 --> 00:26:10,380
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

444
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,800
[Wucheng Gate]

445
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:27,110
Your Majesty,

446
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,410
your wound had already healed.

447
00:26:29,750 --> 00:26:31,610
How can it tear open like this now?

448
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,820
There was an assassin yesterday.

449
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:46,740
Alright, Your Majesty.

450
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,730
Don't stare.

451
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,070
Your Majesty,
you need to restrain yourself.

452
00:26:57,070 --> 00:26:59,400
I'll go prepare your medicine right away.

453
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,160
The medicine box.

454
00:27:07,570 --> 00:27:08,840
What an assassin.

455
00:27:09,310 --> 00:27:10,960
She left me covered in wounds

456
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,700
and even scared Physician Xiao away.

457
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:15,480
Then blame yourself

458
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,460
for being that devastatingly handsome.

459
00:27:19,030 --> 00:27:20,790
Which woman at my age

460
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,730
could resist such temptation?

461
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:24,790
Wanyin,

462
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,950
be gentler next time.

463
00:27:28,790 --> 00:27:29,970
We'll see then.

464
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:31,830
You'll be late for the morning court.

465
00:27:31,830 --> 00:27:32,720
Let's go now.

466
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:35,150
It's just being late
for the morning court.

467
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:38,130
There's still a long way to go before I

468
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:40,440
abandon the morning court entirely
for you.

469
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,720
So you're saying

470
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:44,100
I should keep up the good work?

471
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:46,840
It seems my dear
still has plenty of energy.

472
00:27:48,110 --> 00:27:50,240
The one who should keep up the good work

473
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:51,350
is me.

474
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:57,250
We'd better
follow the doctor's instructions.

475
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:05,610
What's this?

476
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:07,570
Xiahou Bo did it.

477
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:09,530
In the carriage yesterday.

478
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,880
After hiding for so long,

479
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,380
we still couldn't keep you
out of his notice.

480
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,460
There's nothing we can do.

481
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,180
From the moment he knew

482
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,030
I had the foresight,

483
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:35,010
there were only 2 possible outcomes
for me with him:

484
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,500
either to be used by him

485
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,110
or to die.

486
00:28:45,070 --> 00:28:46,730
Neither of these two outcomes

487
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:48,240
will happen.

488
00:28:51,270 --> 00:28:52,670
Whether in life or death,

489
00:28:53,550 --> 00:28:54,920
I will never leave you.

490
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:01,040
I trust you.

491
00:29:11,070 --> 00:29:13,440
Since he'll suspect us no matter what,

492
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,070
we might as well go all in.

493
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,440
How?

494
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,440
A straight.

495
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,220
Look at this hand.

496
00:29:25,510 --> 00:29:26,440
What great luck.

497
00:29:27,790 --> 00:29:28,880
A straight, huh?

498
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:30,550
Wait.

499
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:31,580
Don't rush.

500
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:34,050
Let me see.

501
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,200
Break up this pair.

502
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:38,760
Put this here.

503
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,140
There, that's a straight.

504
00:29:41,830 --> 00:29:42,490
I'll cover.

505
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:45,530
Right, right.

506
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,570
It covered that.

507
00:29:49,750 --> 00:29:50,720
You.

508
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:53,050
You're quite good at it.

509
00:29:54,830 --> 00:29:55,640
Lord Yu.

510
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:58,830
Eunuch An?

511
00:29:58,870 --> 00:30:00,130
You... How come you...

512
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:04,550
Wait, wait. I...

513
00:30:04,570 --> 00:30:06,030
I was just playing for fun.

514
00:30:06,030 --> 00:30:07,560
I wasn't gambling, really.

515
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,070
They're all my servants.

516
00:30:09,270 --> 00:30:10,150
-You can ask them.
-Yes.

517
00:30:10,150 --> 00:30:11,030
No money involved.

518
00:30:11,030 --> 00:30:11,750
Lord Yu,

519
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:13,320
you're overthinking it.

520
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:15,930
As the father of the Empress,

521
00:30:16,790 --> 00:30:18,050
what's wrong with doing a little gambling?

522
00:30:18,050 --> 00:30:20,110
And what's wrong with playing cards?

523
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,840
The Empress?

524
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:29,240
Just now in court,

525
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:33,690
His Majesty officially declared
Noble Consort Yu as Empress.

526
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:35,700
Imperial Father-in-law,

527
00:30:35,790 --> 00:30:37,270
congratulations.

528
00:30:41,750 --> 00:30:42,270
Master!

529
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:42,750
Lord Yu?

530
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:46,070
Three, two, three, four.

531
00:30:46,510 --> 00:30:48,750
Five, six, seven, eight.

532
00:30:49,030 --> 00:30:49,760
Xie Yong'er.

533
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:50,890
Don't slack off.

534
00:30:51,590 --> 00:30:53,640
Four, two, three, four.

535
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:56,510
-Five, six, seven, eight.
-I didn't expect that

536
00:30:56,510 --> 00:30:57,550
-nearly 10 years after
-Five, two, three, four.

537
00:30:57,550 --> 00:30:59,000
graduating middle school,

538
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,200
I'd be doing broadcast exercises here.

539
00:31:02,310 --> 00:31:04,110
Exercise is important.

540
00:31:04,270 --> 00:31:05,310
Yeah, yeah.

541
00:31:05,550 --> 00:31:06,550
Come on, next set—

542
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:07,740
jumping jacks.

543
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:08,680
Ready, go!

544
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,330
-One, two...
-Stop.

545
00:31:12,750 --> 00:31:14,750
Greetings, Your Majesty.

546
00:31:15,110 --> 00:31:15,970
What are you...

547
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:17,680
doing?

548
00:31:18,030 --> 00:31:19,290
Broadcast exercises.

549
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,310
Your Majesty,

550
00:31:20,310 --> 00:31:21,270
would you like to join us?

551
00:31:21,270 --> 00:31:21,890
Yes, yes.

552
00:31:22,270 --> 00:31:24,270
Her Majesty has been teaching us
lots of exercises lately.

553
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:25,310
They're all actually fun.

554
00:31:25,310 --> 00:31:26,550
My sleep

555
00:31:26,550 --> 00:31:27,920
has actually improved a lot.

556
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,920
Her Majesty even taught us a slogan:

557
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:31,880
"Get moving, focus on yourself,

558
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,680
purify the environment, start with me."

559
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,640
What do you think?

560
00:31:41,490 --> 00:31:43,820
So all this time
you've been standing me up

561
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:45,550
just to do this?

562
00:31:45,830 --> 00:31:46,590
Or what else?

563
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,440
I'm the Empress now,

564
00:31:49,590 --> 00:31:50,830
their boss.

565
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:53,810
You care about the empire in court,

566
00:31:53,830 --> 00:31:55,030
so I certainly need to care about

567
00:31:55,030 --> 00:31:57,560
the quality of life
for the women in the harem.

568
00:31:58,550 --> 00:31:59,810
I live in the harem too.

569
00:32:00,790 --> 00:32:01,990
But my quality of life

570
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:04,520
has been declining sharply.

571
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:05,960
Don't be so dramatic.

572
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:09,690
Alright.

573
00:32:10,350 --> 00:32:10,920
Next,

574
00:32:11,270 --> 00:32:12,830
let's move on to the next exercise.

575
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:14,550
Okay!

576
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:16,810
We need you for this one.

577
00:32:34,990 --> 00:32:35,310
Run!

578
00:32:49,310 --> 00:32:50,180
Run faster!

579
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:01,780
Hurry!

580
00:33:04,350 --> 00:33:05,550
The water's boiling.

581
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:06,770
We can start now.

582
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:07,820
I'm not eating.

583
00:33:08,270 --> 00:33:09,350
So arrogant?

584
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:11,240
Mr. Bei made sour soup hotpot.

585
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,880
Are you really not eating?

586
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:13,680
Are you sure?

587
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:16,610
How did I, a ruler of the nation,

588
00:33:17,510 --> 00:33:20,710
end up playing
"Eagle Catches Chicks" with you in public?

589
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,200
Hotpot?

590
00:33:25,110 --> 00:33:26,310
Just cook me instead.

591
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:31,990
A good emperor
enjoys time with his people.

592
00:33:32,150 --> 00:33:34,480
Besides, weren't you having fun just now?

593
00:33:37,550 --> 00:33:40,280
Physician Xiao said
you need moderate exercise.

594
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:42,210
I was doing this for your own good.

595
00:33:43,270 --> 00:33:44,930
Everything is for my own good.

596
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,920
You're closer

597
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:49,400
to those consorts

598
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:50,270
than to me now.

599
00:33:52,740 --> 00:33:54,750
I should've just kept you
in the Cold Palace

600
00:33:54,750 --> 00:33:56,350
Playing with them every day?

601
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,980
You're jealous?

602
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:00,790
Who's jealous?

603
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,680
Of those consorts?

604
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:04,880
Dan,

605
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,750
Eunuch An sent word

606
00:34:06,830 --> 00:34:08,760
that the Empress Dowager is dying.

607
00:34:09,510 --> 00:34:10,710
Didn't Physician Xiao say

608
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:12,570
she could hold on a little longer?

609
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:15,590
How could my mother

610
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:17,719
let everything go my way?

611
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,060
I'll see her off one last time.

612
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:24,730
I'll go with you.

613
00:34:25,230 --> 00:34:26,920
His Majesty has arrived!

614
00:34:27,230 --> 00:34:27,710
Mother!

615
00:34:30,670 --> 00:34:31,670
Physician Zhang!

616
00:34:32,230 --> 00:34:33,670
Why did Mother pass away so suddenly?

617
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:34,469
Your Majesty,

618
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:36,960
Her Majesty hasn't passed away yet.

619
00:34:40,250 --> 00:34:40,810
Mother,

620
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,739
I've come to see you one last time.

621
00:34:43,940 --> 00:34:44,540
-Your Majesty!
-Your Majesty!

622
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:46,270
-Your Majesty!
-Your Majesty!

623
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:50,650
Leave us, all of you.

624
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,860
Greetings, Your Majesty.

625
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:54,600
How is she?

626
00:34:55,110 --> 00:34:56,280
I've administered acupuncture.

627
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,150
At most, it will hold for 7 to 8 minutes.

628
00:34:58,150 --> 00:34:59,010
That's enough.

629
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,560
Mother, don't worry.

630
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:10,510
Though we've fought for so long,

631
00:35:12,150 --> 00:35:14,550
I won't hold grudges
against a dead person.

632
00:35:15,690 --> 00:35:18,150
You will still be buried
as Empress Dowager.

633
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,680
In the history books,

634
00:35:20,590 --> 00:35:21,920
you'll have your place.

635
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:30,400
Since you can't bear
to leave your beloved little prince,

636
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:31,200
I

637
00:35:31,670 --> 00:35:32,870
will make him a prince

638
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:38,350
and have him live permanently at
the imperial mausoleum with you. Alright?

639
00:35:43,550 --> 00:35:46,350
You needn't worry about my throne
lacking an heir.

640
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:49,290
I have already crowned an empress.

641
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,240
In the future,

642
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:55,030
there will naturally
be a new crown prince.

643
00:35:58,400 --> 00:35:59,030
Forget it.

644
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:07,190
Is there any way

645
00:36:07,630 --> 00:36:09,090
to make her speak clearly?

646
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:31,230
Xiahou Dan...

647
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,880
you're ruthless enough.

648
00:36:37,190 --> 00:36:39,670
You really are the child I raised.

649
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:41,690
I'm ashamed.

650
00:36:43,550 --> 00:36:45,350
I only learned a little from you.

651
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:48,000
You won't

652
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,710
have a good ending.

653
00:36:55,590 --> 00:36:56,960
Fine. I'll be waiting.

654
00:36:59,510 --> 00:37:00,710
If you're still alive

655
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:03,480
and want revenge,

656
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:05,960
come find me anytime.

657
00:37:08,030 --> 00:37:09,480
I don't hate you.

658
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,190
I don't hate anyone.

659
00:37:15,550 --> 00:37:17,280
I just had bad luck

660
00:37:18,150 --> 00:37:20,400
and chose the wrong poison.

661
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:33,880
Do you know

662
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,290
why you have been suffering

663
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:41,590
from headaches all these years?

664
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:44,660
Why?

665
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:48,280
Come here,

666
00:37:50,190 --> 00:37:51,320
and I'll tell you.

667
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,200
Explain yourself clearly.

668
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:55,630
Come here.

669
00:38:03,710 --> 00:38:04,390
Why?

670
00:38:04,550 --> 00:38:05,950
Let go of my grandmother!

671
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:08,700
-There's poison!
-Your Majesty!

672
00:38:23,070 --> 00:38:23,750
Go!

673
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:25,510
Go.

674
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,150
Your Majesty!

675
00:38:32,150 --> 00:38:32,950
Your Majesty!

676
00:38:33,710 --> 00:38:34,510
The antidote.

677
00:38:36,030 --> 00:38:36,960
The antidote!

678
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:38,920
Your Majesty!

679
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:39,720
Your Majesty!

680
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,680
Give me the antidote!

681
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,580
Where is the antidote?

682
00:38:44,670 --> 00:38:45,600
Give it to me now!

683
00:38:47,940 --> 00:38:50,400
Don't you want your little Crown Prince
to live?

684
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:52,480
-Give me the antidote!
-If anything happens to her,

685
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,400
you'll all die!

686
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:55,300
-Your Majesty.
-No, Your Majesty!
